Business Brief -- Stuart Hall Co.:
   Company Enters Into Talks
   On Its Purchase by Newell
Stuart Hall said the talks began as its officials were
negotiating a definitive form of a letter of intent the
companies signed last October, under which Newell was to
acquire a stake of about 18% in Stuart Hall by purchasing
750,000 shares of a new class of preferred for $10.5 million.
   The company said a special committee of outside directors,
which had previously been appointed to consider the original
transactions, will now "expand its scope of action to
evaluate" the possible acquisition of the entire company by
Newell.
   Stuart Hall has about 3.95 million shares currently
outstanding.
   In national over-the-counter trading yesterday, Stuart
Hall shares closed at $9.375, up 12.5 cents.